[[File:Zypern aus dem Weltall gesehen.jpg|thumb|Cyprus from Space]] [[File:SolarGIS-Solar-map-Cyprus-tr.png|thumb|Solar Map of the Island]] [[File:Kyrenia from St Hilarion.jpg|thumb|Mountainous Geography from Northern Side]] [[File:Aphrodites Rock.jpg|thumb|Seacoast from Southern Side]] [[File:Камни Афродиты 2011 октябрь на закате.jpg|thumb|Sunsets on the island]] [[File:Protaras tropical famous beach at Paralimni holiday destination in Republic of Cyprus.jpg|thumb|Seacoast from Eastern side]] [[Cyprus]] has a [[Subtropical|subtropical climate]] - [[Mediterranean climate|Mediterranean]] and [[Semi-arid climate|semi-arid]] type (in the north-eastern part of island) - according to [[Köppen climate classification]] signes ''[[Mediterranean climate|Csa]]'' and ''[[Semi-arid climate|BSh]]'',<ref>{{cite journal |author1=Peel, M. C. |author2=Finlayson B. L. |author3=McMahon, T. A. |last-author-amp=yes | year=2007 | title= Updated world map of the Köppen–Geiger climate classification | journal=Hydrol. Earth Syst. Sci. | volume=11 | pages=1633–1644 | url=http://www.hydrol-earth-syst-sci.net/11/1633/2007/hess-11-1633-2007.html |doi=10.5194/hess-11-1633-2007| issn = 1027-5606}} ''(direct: [http://www.hydrol-earth-syst-sci.net/11/1633/2007/hess-11-1633-2007.pdf Final Revised Paper])''</ref><ref>[https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/mt.html#Geo CIA Factbook] - Geographic location</ref> with very mild winters (on the coast) and warm to hot summers. Snow is possible only in the [[Troodos mountains]] in the central part of the island. Rain occurs mainly in winter, with summer being generally dry.
== Temperatures == Cyprus has one of the warmest climates and warmest winters in the [[Mediterranean]] part of the [[European Union]]. The average annual temperature on the coast is around {{convert|24|°C|°F|abbr=on}} during the day and {{convert|14|°C|°F|abbr=on}} at night. Generally – warm temperature season lasts about eight months. It begins in April, with average temperatures of {{convert|21|-|23|C|F}} during the day and {{convert|11|-|13|C|F}} at night, and ends in November, with average temperatures of {{convert|22|-|23|C|F}} during the day and {{convert|12|-|14|C|F}} at night. In the remaining four months of the year, the temperatures tend to remain mild, while sometimes exceed {{convert|20|°C|0|abbr=on}} during the day. In [[Limassol]], in the period January–February, the average maximum temperature is {{convert|17|-|18|C|F}} during the day and {{convert|8|-|9|C|F}} at night. In other coastal locations in Cyprus, the temperature is generally {{convert|16|-|17|C|F}} during the day and {{convert|6|-|9|C|F}} at night. In March and December in Limassol the average is {{convert|19|-|20|C|F}} during the day and {{convert|10|-|11|C|F}} at night; other coastal locations in Cyprus are generally {{convert|17|-|19|C|F}} during the day and {{convert|8|-|11|C|F}} at night.
The middle of summer (July and August) is usually hot, with an average maximum coastal temperature of around {{convert|35|°C|°F|abbr=on}} during the day and around {{convert|25|°C|°F|abbr=on}} at night. In the centre of the island – the highlands – the average temperature exceeds {{convert|35|°C|°F|abbr=on}}). In June and September on the coast the average maximum temperature is usually around {{convert|28|-|30|C|F}} during the day and around {{convert|18|-|20|C|F}} at night. While large temperature fluctuations are rare on the coast, the centre of Cyprus has more variations – typically colder winters and hotter summers.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.moa.gov.cy/moa/MS/MS.nsf/DMLclimet_reports_en/DMLclimet_reports_en?OpenDocument&Start=1&Count=1000&Expand=1|title=Meteorological Service - Climatological and Meteorological Reports|accessdate=}}</ref>
== Temperature of sea == The average annual temperature of the sea around Cyprus is {{convert|21|-|22|C|F}}, from {{convert|17|°C|°F|abbr=on}} in February to {{convert|27|-|28|C|F}} in August (depending on the location). In the seven months from May to November the average sea temperature exceeds {{convert|20|°C|°F|abbr=on}}.<ref name="weather2travel">{{cite web|url=http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/cyprus/ |title=Cyprus Climate Guide |accessdate=5 June 2009}}</ref>
{| class="wikitable" |+ Sea temperature |- ! !'''Jan''' !'''Feb''' !'''Mar''' !'''Apr''' !'''May''' !'''Jun''' !'''Jul''' !'''Aug''' !'''Sep''' !'''Oct''' !'''Nov''' !'''Dec''' |- | [[Paphos]] [http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/cyprus/paphos.php] | 18 | 17 | 17 | 18 | 20 | 24 | 26 | 27 | 26 | 24 | 22 | 19 |- | [[Larnaca]] [http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/cyprus/larnaca.php] | 18 | 17 | 17 | 18 | 20 | 24 | 26 | 27 | 27 | 25 | 22 | 19 |- | [[Limassol]] [http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/cyprus/limassol.php] | 18 | 17 | 17 | 18 | 20 | 24 | 26 | 27 | 27 | 25 | 22 | 19 |- | [[Argaka]] [http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/cyprus/argaka.php] | | | | | | | | | | | | |- | [[Ayia Napa]] [http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/cyprus/ayia-napa.php] | | | | | | | | | | | | |- | [[Coral Bay, Cyprus|Coral Bay]] [http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/cyprus/coral-bay.php] | | | | | | | | | | | | |- | [[Famagusta]] [http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/cyprus/famagusta.php] | | | | | | | | | | | | |- | [[Kyrenia]] [http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/cyprus/kyrenia.php] | | | | | | | | | | | | |- | [[Latchi]] [http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/cyprus/latchi.php] | | | | | | | | | | | | |- | [[Nissi Bay]] [http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/cyprus/nissi-bay.php] | | | | | | | | | | | | |- | [[Peyia]] [http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/cyprus/peyia.php] | | | | | | | | | | | | |- | [[Polis]] [http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/cyprus/polis.php] | | | | | | | | | | | | |- | [[Protaras]] [http://www.weather2travel.com/climate-guides/cyprus/protaras.php] | | | | | | | | | | | | |}
== Sunshine == Cyprus receives an average of 2,700 to 3,500 hours per year. In winter, Cyprus receives an average of 5–6 hours of sunlight per day, half of the 12–13 hours experienced at the height of summer.<ref name="weather2travel"/> This is about double that of cities in the northern half of Europe; for comparison, [[London]] has 1,461 hours.<ref name=London_climate>{{cite web |url = http://www.metoffice.gov.uk/climate/uk/averages/19712000/sites/greenwich.html |title = Met Office: Climate averages 1971-2000 |publisher = [[Met Office]] |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/5wpl3HnmR?url=http://www.metoffice.gov.uk/climate/uk/averages/19712000/sites/greenwich.html |archivedate = 2011-02-28 |df = }}</ref> However, in winter there can be more than four times more sunshine; for comparison, London has 37 hours<ref name=London_climate /> while coastal locations in Cyprus have around 180 hours of sunshine in December (that is, as much as in May in London).
