The '''Tagaytay–Nasugbu Highway''' (or '''Tagaytay–Nasugbu Road''') is a {{convert|43.86|km|adj=on}}, two-to-four lane, secondary highway in the provinces of [[Cavite]] and [[Batangas]], [[Philippines]], that connects the city of [[Tagaytay]] in [[Cavite]] and the municipality of [[Nasugbu, Batangas|Nasugbu]] in [[Batangas]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dpwh.gov.ph/dpwh/2016%20DPWH%20ATLAS/Road%20Data%202016/batangas_1st.htm|title=Batangas 1st|website=www.dpwh.gov.ph|access-date=2018-01-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dpwh.gov.ph/dpwh/2016%20DPWH%20ATLAS/Road%20Data%202016/cavite_sub.htm|title=Cavite 2nd|website=www.dpwh.gov.ph|access-date=2018-01-09}}</ref>

Under the implementation of the route numbering system by the  [[Department of Public Works and Highways]] in 2014, the entire road is a component of '''National Route 410''' ('''N410''') in the Cavite province, and '''National Route 407''' ('''N407''') in the Batangas province of the [[Philippine highway network]].

==Route description==
The highway starts at Tagaytay Rotunda, where it intersects with [[Tagaytay–Calamba Road]] and Tagaytay–Talisay Road.

